article.headline: Boise State routs Northwest Nazarene 91-51
article.story: BOISE, Idaho -- Derrick Marks scored 19 points, James Webb III scored a career-high 18 points and grabbed a career-high 11 rebounds, and Boise State routed Division II Northwest Nazarene 91-51 on Thursday night. Northwest Nazarene led 7-4 on a 3-pointer by Aubrey Ball, but Boise State took charge with a 23-1 run. Web scored nine points in the half and the Broncos were up 41-20 at the break, their largest halftime lead of the season. Webb opened the second half with a layup and a 3-pointer to spark a 16-3 run and the Broncos cruised, leading by as many as 44 points. Igor Hadziomerovic had six assists for the Broncos (7-2) and Montigo Alford had four assists. Ball led the Crusaders (2-8) with 13 points, including three 3-pointers. Kevin Rima added 11 points while Erik Kinney had 10.
